---
// src/pages/terms.astro
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
import NavBlock from "../components/NavBlock.astro";

const effectiveDate = "June 2, 2026";
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Terms of Service | Quirgs"
  description="Terms of service for the Quirgs AI governance skills registry."
  terminalPath="~/terms"
>
  <NavBlock currentPath="/terms/" />

  <div class="line">
    <span class="prompt">admin@quirgs</span><span class="path">~/terms</span
    ><span class="text-bright">$</span>&nbsp;cat terms.md
  </div>
  <div class="line">&nbsp;</div>

  <div class="detail-header">
    <h1 class="text-bright">Terms of Service</h1>
    <p class="tagline">Conditions for using quirgs.com and its skills.</p>
  </div>

  <div class="terminal-body" style="padding: 0;">
    <p><strong class="text-bright">Effective date:</strong> {effectiveDate}</p>

    <h2>1. Acceptance</h2>
    <p>
      By accessing or using quirgs.com, you agree to these Terms of Service. If
      you do not agree, do not use this site.
    </p>

    <h2>2. What Quirgs provides</h2>
    <p>
      Quirgs is a registry of AI governance skills, guides, and tools. Content
      is provided for informational and integration purposes. Skills published
      here are designed for use with compatible AI agent platforms (e.g.,
      Claude, Cowork).
    </p>
    <p>
      Nothing on quirgs.com constitutes legal, compliance, or regulatory advice.
      Governance skills are reference implementations — you are responsible for
      validating their suitability for your specific regulatory context before
      deploying them in production.
    </p>

    <h2>3. Use of the site</h2>
    <p>You agree not to:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>
        Scrape, mirror, or systematically copy content without permission.
      </li>
      <li>
        Use the site in any way that violates applicable law or regulation.
      </li>
      <li>
        Attempt to reverse-engineer, disable, or interfere with site
        infrastructure.
      </li>
      <li>
        Represent Quirgs skills as your own original work for commercial
        redistribution without modification.
      </li>
    </ul>

    <h2>4. Skill licenses</h2>
    <p>
      Each skill published on quirgs.com is distributed via a public GitHub
      Gist. The applicable license is specified in the Gist. Where no license is
      specified, skills are provided for personal and organizational evaluation
      use only — redistribution requires written permission.
    </p>
    <p>
      Skills may be integrated into your own AI workflows and agent
      configurations without restriction, provided you do not redistribute them
      as a standalone product.
    </p>

    <h2>5. Disclaimer of warranties</h2>
    <p>
      quirgs.com and all skills are provided <strong class="text-bright"
        >"as is"</strong
      >, without warranty of any kind, express or implied, including but not
      limited to warranties of merchantability, fitness for a particular
      purpose, or non-infringement. We do not warrant that skills will produce
      legally compliant outputs in your jurisdiction or for your specific use
      case.
    </p>

    <h2>6. Limitation of liability</h2>
    <p>
      To the maximum extent permitted by applicable law, Quirgs and its
      operators shall not be liable for any indirect, incidental, special,
      consequential, or punitive damages arising from your use of this site or
      its skills, even if advised of the possibility of such damages.
    </p>

    <h2>7. Third-party links and tools</h2>
    <p>
      quirgs.com links to external resources (GitHub Gists, documentation, AI
      platform providers). We are not responsible for the content, availability,
      or privacy practices of third-party sites. Links are provided for
      convenience only.
    </p>

    <h2>8. Intellectual property</h2>
    <p>
      The Quirgs name, logo, and brand assets are proprietary. Site content,
      page layouts, and design are copyright Quirgs unless otherwise noted.
      Skill content distributed via public Gists is licensed per the terms in
      each Gist.
    </p>

    <h2>9. Changes to these terms</h2>
    <p>
      We may update these terms at any time. The effective date at the top will
      reflect the latest revision. Continued use of quirgs.com after a change
      constitutes acceptance of the updated terms.
    </p>

    <h2>10. Governing law</h2>
    <p>
      These terms are governed by the laws of the State of California, United
      States, without regard to its conflict of law provisions.
    </p>

    <div class="line">&nbsp;</div>
    <div>
      Questions? See <a href="/support/">/support/</a>.
    </div>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>
